\section{Overview}

% Updated July 15 2025 by BCP from Simon's description in MaxVerse doc

\begin{itemize}
\item {\bf Source Verse} (\Cref{fig:source-verse-expr,fig:source-verse-expr2}) is an approximation of the full source language.
\item The \emph{superficial-desugar} pass desugars
(\Cref{fig:sv-to-sv-1,fig:sv-to-sv-2}) Source Verse into
  {\bf Essential Verse} (\Cref{fig:small-source-verse}), whose distinctive feature is TimLambdas.
  Essential Verse is a subset of Source Verse.
\item A \emph{wrapping transformation} (\Cref{fig:mini-verse}) further
desugars Essential Verse into {\bf Mini Verse}
(\Cref{fig:mini-verse}).
\item A \emph{translation for verification and execution}
(\Cref{fig:ds12})
takes Mini Verse to {\bf Core Verse} (\Cref{fig:core-verse}).  The
operational semantics of Core Verse in terms of rewrite and
verification rules is defined in \Crefrange{fig:vc-syntax}{fig:verifier-rules-arrays}.
(As of July 2025, \Cref{fig:vc-contexts} is out of date.  Not clear
how \Cref{fig:ds12} fits in.)
\item We are currently experimenting with three different approaches
to the {\bf denotational semantics} of Mini Verse. (Tim and Koen prefer DPS;
Simon finds expression style easier to grok.)
\Cref{fig:densem-notation} defines some common notations.
\begin{enumerate}
\item \textbf{(E-LV)}: expression-style, list of values.
  \begin{itemize}
  \item $\semappsub{E}{e}{|e|} : \Env \rightarrow \seq{ \VAL }$
  \item \Cref{fig:e-lv1} and \Cref{fig:e-lv2}
    \end{itemize}
\item \textbf{(D-LS)}: dps-style, list of sets of environments.
  \begin{itemize}
  \item $\semapsub{E}{d}{|e|} r : \seq{ \ENV }$
  \item \Cref{fig:d-ls1} and \Cref{fig:d-ls2}
    \end{itemize}
\item \textbf{(D-SLS)}: dps-style, sets of lists of sets of environments.
  \begin{itemize}
  \item $\semapsub{E}{d}{|e|} r : \powersetnp{\seq{ \ENV }}$
  \item \Cref{fig:d-sls1} and \Cref{fig:d-sls2}
    \end{itemize}
\end{enumerate}
\item \Cref{fig:jan-style-dps-1,fig:jan-style-dps-2}
are work in progress on a ``Jan-style'' variant of the DPS semantics.
\item Lennart is working on reviving a ``direct denotational
semantics'' for Essential Verse  (\Crefrange{fig:den-sem1}{fig:den-sem-dest1}).
\end{itemize}

