\section{Denotational semantics: overview}

Design variants (all of them use notation in \Cref{fig:densem-sets-and-seqs} and \Cref{fig:densem-notation}):
\begin{itemize}
\item \textbf{(S-LS)}: semantics of Essential Verse, lists of sets of environments.
  \begin{itemize}
  \item $\semess{S}{u}{v}{|t|} : \seq{ \ENV }$
  \item \Cref{fig:s-ls}
  \end{itemize}

\item \textbf{(E-LS)}: expression-style, list of sets of values.
  \begin{itemize}
  \item $\semappsub{E}{e}{|e|} : \Env \rightarrow \seq{ \VAL }$
  \item \Cref{fig:e-lv1} and \Cref{fig:e-lv2}
  \end{itemize}

\item \textbf{(D-LS)}: dps-style, list of sets of environments.
  \begin{itemize}
  \item $\semapsub{E}{d}{|e|} r : \seq{ \ENV }$
  \item \Cref{fig:d-ls1} and \Cref{fig:d-ls2}
  \end{itemize}

\item \textbf{(D-SLS)}: dps-style, sets of lists of sets of environments.
  \begin{itemize}
  \item $\semapsub{E}{d}{|e|} r : \powersetnp{\seq{ \ENV }}$
  \item \Cref{fig:d-sls1} and \Cref{fig:d-sls2}
  \end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

